page.title: 10MRS. MACDOUGALL'S DAY. PART2
page.content:
02.05p.m.ATTENDED TO PETROL PUMP. 06.00p.m.RUSHED HOME TO MAKE TEA FOR FAMILY(ROLLS AND SOUP). 06.45p.m.SET OUT FOR DALAVICH(8miles) TO ATTEND BROWNIE PACKS 75th BIRTHDAY AND RETIREMENT PRESENTATION OF BROWN OWL, NURSE BROWN,THE LOCAL DISTRICT NURSE. 09.00p.m.RETURNED HOME AND WASHED ALL THE TEA TOWELS FROM THE BAR, WHICH IS PART OF THE CO-OP. 09.30p.m.FINALLY SAT DOWN AND WATCHED A LATE NIGHT MOVIE ON TELEVISION. 01.30a.m.WENT TO BED.
Mrs.MacDougall travelled approximately 50 miles that day which is not exceptional for her,she also cooks in a local hotel in the summer season evenings only!
